<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hector" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hector,</orth> 1) the Trojan hero: <bibl n="shak. luc 1430" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1430</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 1430" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1430</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.196" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 196</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.537" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 537</bibl>. 636 etc. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.237" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 237</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 3, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.8.25" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 8, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.1.36" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 1, 36</bibl> and passim. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.3.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 3, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.8.11" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 8, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.1.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. IV, 1, 88</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.8.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 8, 7</bibl>. His name used appellatively to denote highest valour: Wiv, <bibl n="shak. ant 1.3.12" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 35</bibl> (the host's speech).<lb />2) a usual name of dogs: <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.665" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 665</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>